                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="avalon_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="dis-g"><span class="wrap">(</span><span class="dtxt">in ancient stories</span><span class="wrap">)</span></span></span> <span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a beautiful island where dead heroes go. According to the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/legend#legend_topg_1" title="legend definition"><span class="ndv">legend</span></a> <span class="gloss" hclass="gloss" htag="span">(= story from ancient times)</span> it is the place where <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/king-arthur#king_arthur_topg_1" title="King Arthur's definition"><span class="ndv">King Arthur's</span></a> body was taken after his last battle. Some people believe Avalon to be in or near what is now <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/glastonbury" title="Glastonbury definition"><span class="ndv">Glastonbury</span></a>.</span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
